          "Acupuncture is thus a wellness therapy that aims to promote physical and mental healing by helping the body regain its overall balance, which in turn promotes spiritual, physical, and emotional health. The treatment involves inserting specialized filiform needles into specific points, typically penetrating between 0.25 to 1.5 inches into the skin. The depth varies based on factors such as the area being treated, the patient’s body type, and the therapeutic goals.",
